        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-6758",
        "content": "Kneeling by the bed was the eldest daughter of the expiring woman, reciting the Litany of the Dying, and the sons and another daughter and a daughter in law repeated the responses in voices broken with tears.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-low_s-normal_e-normal",
